      • getEmptyPagelLabel

        public java.lang.String getEmptyPagelLabel()
        Returns the text to be displayed in the navigation area if no data is available. By default this returns a static label generated from the component name which can be set with setEmptyPageLabel(String). But subclasses can also choose to override this method to return a label that has been generated from the current state.
        Returns:
        The empty page label
